[{"id":"FT548944","type":"longtextV2","stimulusHtml":"The work on the left is Ernst Ludwig Kirchner’s <em>Street, Dresden</em> (1908). The work on the right is Fernand Léger’s <em>The City</em> (1919).Both works show interpretations of the modern urban environment in the early twentieth century. Using specific evidence, analyze how the works reflect the artists’ contrasting interpretations of the modern urban environment.&nbsp;","features":[{"type":"sharedpassage","html":"<p><img alt=\"The image is of an expressionist painting of a street with many people. The street is a pink color and in the forefront of the painting is a woman in a green dress with a hat looking forward. Behind her and towards the right is another woman wearing a large hat, a yellow jacket and a blue skirt with yellow ruffles underneath. The coloring of her skin looks green. Off to the side are two more women looking forward in hats and blue dresses. Behind the main woman in the green dress and to the left is a small child in the street with long orange hair an d a black outfit. Towards the upper left of the piece is a crowd of women looking away. They are all wearing hats and dresses.\" height=\"394\" src=\"https://assets.learnosity.com/organisations/537/media.academicmerit.com/4e745cfe945e08ae08fe232327f86efe/original.png\" width=\"500\" /></p>\n\n<p>LEFT</p>\n\n<p><img alt=\"The image is a painting done in the cubist style. It contains many shapes and basic figures over layered over one another. The colors used are red, green, blue, magenta, yellow, black and white. Some of the objects are shaded while others are solid colors.\" height=\"406\" src=\"https://assets.learnosity.com/organisations/537/media.academicmerit.com/052b33724fb92e52482efc994c57de7f/original.png\" width=\"500\" /></p>\n\n<p>RIGHT</p>\n"}]}]